- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the termination of higher-order rewriting and beta-reduction, which are topics related to logic and computation. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also a likely category as the paper discusses the extension of the higher-order recursive path ordering to richer type systems, which is a topic related to programming languages. 
- cs.TL (Temporal Logic) and cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) are less likely categories, but they may still be relevant as the paper deals with the well-foundedness of orderings and closure properties, which are topics related to temporal logic and formal languages. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the least likely category, but it may still be relevant as the paper discusses the ordering of computations and the termination of algorithms.
